LAGOS – Abdel Fatah El-Sisi, President of Egypt, has tasked the government agencies in the country to facilitate the upgrading of facilities and infrastructure in the five designated cities that would host the forthcoming Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON). The five designated cities, namely Alexandria, Cairo, Ismailia, Suez and Port Said, will host the 32nd edition of the Africa Cup of Nations, which will take place from June 21 to July 19, 2019. “The government agencies must be up doing in the upgrading of facilities specifically in the areas of Stadia, Medical, Transportation and Communication,” he said. El-Sisi mad this known at the weekend when Ahmad Ahmad, President of the Confederation of Africa Football (CAF), paid him a courtesy call at the Presidential Palace in Cairo to discuss the impending Total Africa Cup of Nations amongst others. DAILY INDEPENDENT gathered that during the meeting, El-Sisi emphasised the need for effective coordination between the related agencies to ensure a successful tournament that will meet both continental and international standards. El-Sisis, who was recently elected Chairperson of the African Union (AU) during the body’s Ordinary Session few weeks ago in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, underscored the role of sports especially football in promoting peace and unity on the continent. On his part, CAF President Ahmad lauded his Egyptian counterpart for the huge interest towards a successful AFCON, which will have 24 teams for the first time. He later presented a symbolic pennant to the Egyptian President, assuring the commitment to hosting a memorable tournament. Also present were Egyptian Prime Minister, Moustafa Madbouli and Minister of Youth and Sports, Ashraf Sobhi. The Super Eagles will lead 23 other soccer playing Nations in the continent to the AFCON tournament in Egypt, even though they have their last qualifiers against Seychelles to play.